versity and the people working within it continue to keep their traditionally marginalized members relegated to symbolic status, somewhere outside the center. Reyes confronts the impossibility of success in the midst of competing and contradictory needs—from navigating coded language, to balancing professional expectations with care-taking responsibilities, to combating the literal exclusions of outmoded and hierarchical rules. Her searing commentary takes on, with sensitivity and fury, the urgent call for academic justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCollege teachersxTenurezUnited States. 0aDiscrimination in higher educationzUnited States. 0aMinority college teacherszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 0aMinority women college teacherszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aRacism in higher educationzUnited States. 0aSexism in higher educationzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh  aacademia.  aadvice.  afaculty.  afeminism.  agender.  agraduate school.  agraduate students.  amemoir.  amotherhood.  arace/ethnicity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107664860 cprintz978150363299840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363368140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503633681423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503633681/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stan